==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Predominance
<hw>Pre*dom"i*nance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧dominance</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being predominant; superiority; ascendency; prevalence;
predomination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>predominance</qex> of conscience over interest.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astrol.)</fld> <def>The superior influence of a
planet.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predominancy</ent>⟦br⟧
